        After walking alongside other souls you find a queue leading to Charon,
        the underworld's ferryman, who takes each soul individually to their new destination.
        </text>
        <options>
            <option description="Wait in line for Charon to take you to the first circle." nextDialogueId="4" />
            <option description="Skip ahead of everyone and get on his boat first." nextDialogueId="2" alternativeNextId="3" reward="5 Sins" />
        </options>
    </dialogue>
    <dialogue id="2">
        <text>
        You throw a rock aside to distract all souls and run to jump on Charon's boat just
        before he reaches the coast. You make it, and he takes you to the first circle while
        hearing all other souls' cries of disgust. You get 5 Sin points.
        </text>
        <nextDialogueId>4</nextDialogueId>
    </dialogue>
    <dialogue id="3">
        <text>
        You throw a rock aside to distract all souls and run to jump on Charon's boat just
        before he reaches the coast. You don't reach the boat and thus fall into the river
        of lost souls to roam it for eternity.
        </text>
        <nextDialogueId>DEATH</nextDialogueId>
    </dialogue>
