        Charon drops you off at river Acheron's coast, and you only have to walk a bit to
        find yourself in the first circle of Hell, the Limbo. The first thing you see is the
        vast Asphodel Meadows where an old man, Virgil, is standing speaking with other
        non-baptised folk. He offers to guide you but only if you decide to face the
        weight of your sins. What do you say?
        </text>
        <options>
            <option description="Accept Virgil's help by facing your sins." nextDialogueId="5"  reward="10 Sins"/>
            <option description="Reject Virgil's offer." nextDialogueId="6" />
        </options>
    </dialogue>
    <dialogue id="5">
        <text>
        You accept Virgil's help, and he guides you to the next phase, while walking towards
        it, you meet several people and try an asphodel, but since you are not dead it has no taste.
        You get 10 Sin points.
        </text>
        <nextDialogueId>7</nextDialogueId>
    </dialogue>
    <dialogue id="6">
        <text>
        After you reject Virgil's offer you start walking towards the end of the Limbo, but
        the furies start appearing everywhere you look, and suddenly they attack you.
        This will be the price to pay for not facing your sins...
        </text>
        <nextDialogueId>furyBattle</nextDialogueId>
    </dialogue>
